### What setup.sh does automatically

1. Clones & installs the battle-tested EverClaw proxy + guardian (Node.js sidecar, ~80 MB total)
2. Starts proxy on boot (systemd user service or launchd)
3. Runs `tinyclaw start` wizard if needed
4. Adds these env vars (so Codex CLI automatically uses Morpheus):

```bash
export OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8083/v1
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-morpheus
```

5. Patches `~/.tinyclaw/settings.json` (backs up original) with Morpheus-ready agents:

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "coder": { "provider": "openai", "model": "glm-5" },
    "writer": { "provider": "openai", "model": "kimi-k2.5" },
    "reviewer": { "provider": "openai", "model": "glm-4.7-flash" }
  },
  "default_provider": "openai",
  "default_model": "glm-5"
}
```

6. Adds the `enable-morpheus` skill so you can say `/enable-morpheus` in any channel to toggle, check proxy health, or reconfigure teams

### Staking (unlimited use â€” same as all EverClaw forks)

```bash
